On the 40th anniversary of Roe v. Wade, the President released a statement reaffirming the commitment to protect women's health and reproductive freedom. The statement emphasizes that government should not interfere in private family matters and that women should have the right to make their own choices about their bodies and healthcare. The President also mentions the Administration's efforts to reduce unintended pregnancies, support maternal and child health, and minimize the need for abortion. The statement concludes by recommitting to supporting women and families in their choices and promoting safe and healthy communities.